Here's my theory: 
This is her guaranteed victim card before the trial even starts. AH & team know this motion is going to get rejected, & she doesn't give a crap about the sanctions. This last "it was already proved in the UK" strategy ISN'T FOR THE JUDGE; it's for the headline-only-reading ignorant, reactionary general public. When she loses, she'll whip this rejected motion out "it should have never gone to trial anyway bc it was already tried in the UK" & boom public opinion validation, public opinion that will not know that she needed to be an actual PARTY in the UK case for it to be considered re-litigation (so what we set case law now in which a witness can claim the defendant's win?), that discovery could not be fully exercised on her bc she was only a witness, etcetcetc. Ppl will just see the surface & agree. I promise that's what she's up to w this BS motion that they KNOW isn't going to fly. It's her save face loser insurance.
